list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Fixed cuda issue with rand pooling

task.summary: Switched from cuda to cpu. Added the pretrained models and datasets. Now simply execute evaluate_model.py with '--model_path models/sgan-p-models' to inspect the .max() call
Investigated training (cpu, gpu) and added evaluation results visualization.
Remove 'contiguous' to make train.py work (trainCPU.py needs contiguous)
Add gpu/cpu command line switch to evaluation script
Add cpu/gpu command line switch to evaluation script
Add cpu/gpu command line switch to training script
fixed CUDA error: Statistics can only be computed when running the scripts on a CPU

Added collision statistics: 1. Total number of collisions out of all frames ever computed 2. Number of situations with collisions out of all situations ever computed (all samples) 3. Total number of situations ever computed (with and without collisions, len(seq_start_end) * num_samples) 4. List of all situations for which a collision has been detected (obs_traj, pred_traj_fake, pred_traj_gt), you can use this to visualize the situations.
Added trajectory visualizations and collision evaluations for different thresholds
